(43, 6, 31, 2, 16, 4, 15, 'He gave them bread from heaven to eat', 'Manna as Divine Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the provision of bread from heaven, highlighting God''s care for His people. In John, the reference to manna connects Jesus'' role as the true bread of life to the miraculous sustenance provided in Exodus.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
