(43, 6, 31, 5, 8, 3, 3, 'bread from heaven to eat', 'Manna as Divine Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the provision of manna as bread from heaven. This connection highlights the theme of reliance on God''s word and sustenance beyond physical bread.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 6, 32, 2, 16, 4, 4, 'bread from heaven', 'Heavenly Bread Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine provision, as both passages discuss bread from heaven. In Exodus, God provides bread to the Israelites, while in John, Jesus identifies himself as the true bread from heaven.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
